nditions panel. Add `--black` color variable. Style includes icon, label, score, and collapsible reasons list. (Fulfills req 2: visual range indicator)","Step 4: Update the sailing-weather.js to render the sea status badge in the conditions panel header area. The badge shows the colored level indicator, label text, and score. Updates when timeline hour changes using hourly sea statuses. (Fulfills req 1+2: interactive global indicator that updates with timeline)","Step 5: Update the sailing-app template to include a placeholder element for the sea status indicator in the conditions panel. (Fulfills req 2: DOM structure for the indicator)","Step 6: Write tests for `computeSeaStatus` covering all 4 tiers (green/yellow/red/black) and edge cases (null wave data, extreme values). Run tests to verify."],"summary":"Add a global sea safety indicator that computes an overall score from current weather conditions (wind speed, gusts, wave height, precipitation, pressure trends) and maps it to a 4-tier color system: **green** (Good to go), **yellow** (Caution), **red** (Dangerous), **black** (Do not go out). The indicator will be computed server-side via a shared function, included in the /api/weather response, and rendered as a prominent badge at the top of the conditions panel. It will also update with the timeline slider as the user scrubs through forecast hours.

